label: Fig. 1
caption: Preoperative photography shows about 1×1 cm sized nodular and pinkish mass in the scalp.

label: Fig. 2
caption: (A) The histopathologic examination shows spindle-shaped cells arranged in whirls and fascicles. The mass is adjacent to arrector pili muscle (black arrows). The tumor margin is irregularly mixed with dermal collagen (yellow arrows) (H&E, ×20). (B) The high-power histologic examination shows the indistinctive cytoplasmic membranes and blunt-ended nuclei. There are no cellular atypia, abnormal mitotic activity or necrosis (H&E, ×400).

label: Fig. 3
caption: Immunohistochemistrical study for alpha-smooth muscle actin confirms the diagnosis of cutaneous leiomyoma (H&E, ×40).

caption: Classic presentation of plaque studded with papules and nodules

label: Figure 3
caption: Photomicrograph of piloleiomyoma showing interlacing bundles of smooth muscle fibers with eosinophilic cytoplasm and spindle-shaped nuclei (H and E, ×100)

label: Figure 4
caption: Piloleiomyoma with prominent arector pili (AP) adjacent to the lesion (H and E, ×200)

label: Figure 5
caption: Large pleomorphic hyperchromatic nuclei. Mitosis is inconspicuous (H and E, ×400)

label: Figure 6
caption: Lymphocyte aggregates in between muscle bundles (H and E, ×200)

caption: Immunohistochemical stain against smooth muscle actin highlighting the tumor (×200)

caption: Intersecting fascicles of spindle cells separated by variably collagenized stroma. (H&E stain).

label: Figure 1
caption: Angioleiomyoma. A) Thin-walled vascular channels (small veins) (H&E; x100). B) Thin and thick-walled vascular channels (H&E; x50). C) Calcification of the vascular walls and hyalinization (H&E;x50). D) Myxoid changes (H&E; x50).

label: Figure 2
caption: Piloleiomyoma. A) Epidermal hyperplasia (H&E; x50). B) Basal hyperpigmentation (H&E; x50). C) Entrapped eccrine glands (H&E; x100). D) Entrapped hair follicle in PLM (H&E; x50).

label: Figure 3
caption: A,B) Smooth muscle hamartoma in two patients. Variable shape, size, and orientation of the smooth muscle bundles in the upper dermis (H&E; x50).

label: Figure 4
caption: A) Leiomyosarcoma (H&E; x50). B) Ulceration (H&E; x50). C) Hyaline degeneration (H&E; x100). D) Myxoid changes (H&E; x100).

label: Figure 5
caption: Leiomyosarcoma. A) Chronic inflammatory cell infiltration around the tumor (H&E; x100). B) Tumor necrosis (H&E; x50).
